description.narrative: Kiribati maintained polio-free status, no cases of measles have been reported in the past decade and in 2017 coverage of MR1 vaccine increased to 75 per cent and DPT3 to 64.7 per cent. Progress was achieved towards hepatitis B control with 61 per cent birth dose coverage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2017
